      <exercise> What does it mean to be a solution to a differential equation?</exercise>

      <exercise> Check if the function <m>y(t)=t+1</m> a particular solution to the following
      differential equation:
      <me>
      \frac{dy}{dt}=\frac{y^{2}-1}{t^{2}+2t}.
      </me></exercise>

      <exercise>Check if the function <m>y(x)=x+x\ln x</m> solves the following initial
      value problem:
      <me>
      x\frac{dy}{dx}=x+y,\,\,\,\,\,\,y(1)=3.
      </me></exercise>

      <exercise> Find the equilibrium solutions to the equation
      <me>
      \frac{dy}{dt}=y^{2}+2y
      </me></exercise>
      <exercise>Find the equilibrium solutions to the equation
      <me>
      \frac{dy}{dt}=y^{4}t-3y^{3}t+2y^{2}t.
      </me></exercise>
      <exercise>Classify the following equations as ODEs or PDEs.
      <ol>
      <li> <m>\frac{dy}{dt}=2yt</m></li>
      <li> <m>\frac{\partial u}{\partial t}=\frac{\partial^{2}u}{\partial x^{2}}</m>

      <p> <em>Fun Fact:</em> This particular PDE is a very famous PDE and is called
      the <em>heat equation</em>. It models the flow of heat in a medium over
      time.</p></li>

      <li> <m>\frac{\partial^{2}u}{\partial t^{2}}=\frac{\partial^{2}u}{\partial x^{2}}+\frac{\partial^{2}u}{\partial y^{2}}</m>

      <p><em>Fun Fact:</em> This particular PDE is a very famous PDE and is called
      the <em>wave equation</em>. This PDE along with boundary conditions,
      describes the amplitude and phase of the wave.</p></li>
      <li> <m>x\frac{d^{2}y}{dx^{2}}=y\frac{dy}{dx}+x^{2}y</m></li>
      <li> <m>2y^{\prime\prime}-y^{\prime}+y=0</m></li>
      </ol></exercise>

      <exercise> Classify the order of the following differential equations. Also classify
      if it is linear or nonlinear.
      <ol>
      <li> <m>\frac{dy}{dt}=2yt</m></li>
      <li> <m>y\frac{d^{2}y}{dt^{2}}=\cos t</m></li>
      <li> <m>ty^{\prime\prime\prime}-y^{\prime\prime}-2y=0</m></li>
      <li> <m>\frac{dy^{6}}{dt^{6}}-2\frac{dy}{dt}+y=t^{2}</m></li>
      <li> <m>\cos y+y^{\prime}=t</m></li>
      <li> <m>6y^{\prime\prime\prime}-y^{2}=y^{(5)}</m></li>
      <li> <m>\frac{d^{2}y}{dt^{2}}=\frac{y}{y+t}</m></li>
      </ol>
      </exercise>
