      </me>
      for constant <m>a,b,c</m> where <m>a\ne0</m>, then the exponent <m>r</m> in front
      the <m>t</m> must be a solution to the <em>characteristic equation</em> <m>ar^{2}+br+c=0</m>.</p>
      <p>By yourself, rederive that if <m>y(t)=Ae^{rt}</m> is a solution
      to the equation above, then the number <m>r</m> must satisfy the characteristic equation <m>ar^{2}+br+c=0</m> or <m>A=0</m>. </p>
    </exercise>
